    }
    return Workbook.GetCellStyleAt(0);
}
```

The problem with `GetColumnStyle` is that it always returns something (either the column style or the default style at index 0), so we can't differentiate between "style explicitly set" and "no style set". We need to use a different approach to check if a column style has been set.

Let me look at how `IColumn.IsFormatted` works, or if there's a way to tell if `ColumnStyle` was explicitly set:

